{"parentUuid":"5ea29408-c4bb-4cfd-8a70-dc8b5747989e","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"c2c27b5e-c539-480d-a30b-9f69ca0db082","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a2b2099f1299b45f1","slug":"enumerated-baking-glade","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dhctiecwx2FhzYFrX8CPpW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 711\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/711](https://www.erdosproblems.com/711)\n    23→\n    24→A problem of Erdős and Pomerance on the function $f(n,m)$, the minimal $f$ such that\n    25→in the open interval $(m, m+f)$ there exist distinct integers $a_1, \\ldots, a_n$ with\n    26→$k \\mid a_k$ for all $1 \\leq k \\leq n$.\n    27→\n    28→[ErPo80] Erdős, P. and Pomerance, C., 1980.\n    29→\n    30→[vD26] van Doorn, 2026.\n    31→-/\n    32→\n    33→open Nat\n    34→\n    35→namespace Erdos711\n    36→\n    37→/-- $f(n,m)$ for Erdős Problem 711: the minimal $f$ such that in the open interval\n    38→$(m, m+f)$ there exist $n$ distinct integers $a_1, \\ldots, a_n$ with $k \\mid a_k$ for all\n    39→$1 \\leq k \\leq n$. When $m = n$ this coincides with the function in Problem 710. -/\n    40→noncomputable def f (n m : ℕ) : ℕ :=\n    41→  sInf {f : ℕ | ∃ g : Fin n → ℕ,\n    42→    Function.Injective g ∧\n    43→    (∀ i : Fin n, m < g i) ∧\n    44→    (∀ i : Fin n, g i < m + f) ∧\n    45→    (∀ i : Fin n, (i.val + 1) ∣ g i)}\n    46→\n    47→/--\n    48→Erdős Problem 711, Part 1 [ErPo80]:\n    49→\n    50→Prove that $\\max_m f(n,m) \\leq n^{1+o(1)}$.\n    51→\n    52→Formulated as: for every $\\varepsilon > 0$, there exists $N_0$ such that for all $n \\geq N_0$\n    53→and all $m$,\n    54→$$f(n,m) \\leq n^{1+\\varepsilon}.$$\n    55→\n    56→Erdős and Pomerance proved the weaker bound $\\max_m f(n,m) \\ll n^{3/2}$.\n    57→-/\n    58→@[category research open, AMS 11]\n    59→theorem erdos_711 :\n    60→    ∀ ε : ℝ, 0 < ε →\n    61→    ∃ N₀ : ℕ, ∀ n : ℕ, n ≥ N₀ →\n    62→      ∀ m : ℕ,\n    63→        (f n m : ℝ) ≤ (n : ℝ) ^ (1 + ε) := by\n    64→  sorry\n    65→\n    66→/--\n    67→Erdős Problem 711, Part 2 [ErPo80]:\n    68→\n    69→Prove that $\\max_m (f(n,m) - f(n,n)) \\to \\infty$.\n    70→\n    71→Formulated as: for every $C$, there exists $N_0$ such that for all $n \\geq N_0$,\n    72→there exists $m$ with $f(n,m) \\geq f(n,n) + C$.\n    73→\n    74→van Doorn [vD26] proved that for all large $n$ there exists $m$ with\n    75→$f(n,m) - f(n,n) \\gg (\\log n / \\log \\log n) \\cdot n$.\n    76→-/\n    77→@[category research solved, AMS 11]\n    78→theorem erdos_711.variants.divergence :\n    79→    ∀ C : ℕ, ∃ N₀ : ℕ, ∀ n : ℕ, n ≥ N₀ →\n    80→      ∃ m : ℕ, f n m ≥ f n n + C := by\n    81→  sorry\n    82→\n    83→end Erdos711\n    84→"}]},"uuid":"c415efb7-4501-4570-addf-6ed6993f5f71","timestamp":"2026-03-10T21:32:58.816Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5ea29408-c4bb-4cfd-8a70-dc8b5747989e"}
