{"parentUuid":"6b480164-727d-4f18-9ee2-707a514635e3","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"c2c27b5e-c539-480d-a30b-9f69ca0db082","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a2b2099f1299b45f1","slug":"enumerated-baking-glade","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R4CD5tmyAhcrG9QZGq8kre","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 710\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/710](https://www.erdosproblems.com/710)\n    23→\n    24→Let $f(n)$ be minimal such that in $(n, n+f(n))$ there exist distinct integers\n    25→$a_1, \\ldots, a_n$ such that $k \\mid a_k$ for all $1 \\le k \\le n$. The problem asks\n    26→to obtain an asymptotic formula for $f(n)$.\n    27→\n    28→A problem of Erdős and Pomerance [ErPo80], who proved\n    29→$$\n    30→(2/\\sqrt{e} + o(1)) \\cdot n \\cdot (\\log n / \\log \\log n)^{1/2} \\le f(n)\n    31→\\le (1.7398\\ldots + o(1)) \\cdot n \\cdot (\\log n)^{1/2}.\n    32→$$\n    33→\n    34→See also [711].\n    35→\n    36→[ErPo80] Erdős, P. and Pomerance, C., _Matching the natural numbers up to n with distinct multiples\n    37→in another interval_. Nederl. Akad. Wetensch. Proc. Ser. A 83 (= Indag. Math. 42) (1980), 147-161.\n    38→-/\n    39→\n    40→open Nat\n    41→\n    42→namespace Erdos710\n    43→\n    44→/-- $f(n)$ for Erdős Problem 710: the minimal $f$ such that in the open interval\n    45→$(n, n+f)$ there exist $n$ distinct integers $a_1, \\ldots, a_n$ with $k \\mid a_k$ for all\n    46→$1 \\le k \\le n$. -/\n    47→noncomputable def erdos710F (n : ℕ) : ℕ :=\n    48→  sInf {f : ℕ | ∃ g : Fin n → ℕ,\n    49→    Function.Injective g ∧\n    50→    (∀ i : Fin n, n < g i) ∧\n    51→    (∀ i : Fin n, g i < n + f) ∧\n    52→    (∀ i : Fin n, (i.val + 1) ∣ g i)}\n    53→\n    54→/--\n    55→Erdős Problem 710: Obtain an asymptotic formula for $f(n)$, defined as the minimal $f$ such\n    56→that in $(n, n+f)$ there exist distinct integers $a_1, \\ldots, a_n$ with $k \\mid a_k$ for all\n    57→$1 \\le k \\le n$. The answer is an unknown function $g$ such that $f(n) / g(n) \\to 1$.\n    58→-/\n    59→@[category research open, AMS 11]\n    60→theorem erdos_710 :\n    61→    Filter.Tendsto (fun n : ℕ => (erdos710F n : ℝ) / (answer(sorry) : ℕ → ℝ) n)\n    62→      Filter.atTop (nhds 1) := by\n    63→  sorry\n    64→\n    65→/--\n    66→Erdős Problem 710, known lower bound [ErPo80]:\n    67→\n    68→For every $\\varepsilon > 0$, there exists $N_0$ such that for all $n \\ge N_0$,\n    69→$$\n    70→f(n) \\ge (2/\\sqrt{e} - \\varepsilon) \\cdot n \\cdot (\\log n / \\log \\log n)^{1/2}.\n    71→$$\n    72→-/\n    73→@[category research solved, AMS 11]\n    74→theorem erdos_710.variants.lower :\n    75→    ∀ ε : ℝ, 0 < ε →\n    76→    ∃ N₀ : ℕ, ∀ n : ℕ, n ≥ N₀ →\n    77→      (erdos710F n : ℝ) ≥\n    78→        (2 / (Real.exp 1) ^ ((1 : ℝ) / 2) - ε) * (n : ℝ) *\n    79→        (Real.log (n : ℝ) / Real.log (Real.log (n : ℝ))) ^ ((1 : ℝ) / 2) := by\n    80→  sorry\n    81→\n    82→/--\n    83→Erdős Problem 710, known upper bound [ErPo80]:\n    84→\n    85→For every $\\varepsilon > 0$, there exists $N_0$ such that for all $n \\ge N_0$,\n    86→$$\n    87→f(n) \\le (1.7399 + \\varepsilon) \\cdot n \\cdot (\\log n)^{1/2}.\n    88→$$\n    89→\n    90→The constant $1.7398\\ldots$ comes from the original paper; we use $1.7399$ as\n    91→a rational upper bound on that constant.\n    92→-/\n    93→@[category research solved, AMS 11]\n    94→theorem erdos_710.variants.upper :\n    95→    ∀ ε : ℝ, 0 < ε →\n    96→    ∃ N₀ : ℕ, ∀ n : ℕ, n ≥ N₀ →\n    97→      (erdos710F n : ℝ) ≤\n    98→        (1.7399 + ε) * (n : ℝ) * (Real.log (n : ℝ)) ^ ((1 : ℝ) / 2) := by\n    99→  sorry\n   100→\n   101→end Erdos710\n   102→"}]},"uuid":"42cf66c4-7208-4e3e-9057-a1e1457baf5e","timestamp":"2026-03-10T21:33:04.886Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6b480164-727d-4f18-9ee2-707a514635e3"}
{"parentUuid":"42cf66c4-7208-4e3e-9057-a1e1457baf5e","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"c2c27b5e-c539-480d-a30b-9f69ca0db082","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a2b2099f1299b45f1","slug":"enumerated-baking-glade","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01FkZ3gVUKcM7sNLHBCqWvrH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here's my complete search results:\n\n## Found Files\n\n**Primary File:**\n- `/home/ryan/formal-conjectures/FormalConjectures/ErdosProblems/711.lean`\n\n**Related File (referenced in 711):**\n- `/home/ryan/formal-conjectures/FormalConjectures/ErdosProblems/710.lean`\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n**711.lean** contains the Lean formalization of Erdős Problem 711, which is about the function f(n,m) - the minimal f such that in the open interval (m, m+f) there exist n distinct integers a₁,...,aₙ with k dividing aₖ for all 1 ≤ k ≤ n.\n\nThe file defines:\n1. `f (n m : ℕ) : ℕ` - The main function for the problem\n2. `erdos_711` - Part 1: Prove that max_m f(n,m) ≤ n^(1+o(1))\n3. `erdos_711.variants.divergence` - Part 2: Prove that max_m (f(n,m) - f(n,n)) → ∞\n\nBoth theorems are marked with `sorry` and are currently open research problems, with Part 2 marked as \"solved\" in van Doorn [vD26] with the bound f(n,m) - f(n,n) ≫ (log n / log log n) · n.\n\nThe related **710.lean** file contains the special case where m = n, with corresponding definitions and theorems about lower and upper bounds for that problem.\n\nNo files were found in FormalConjecturesForMathlib specifically related to problem 711."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1953,"cache_read_input_tokens":22017,"output_tokens":420,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1953},